<PB N="54" REF="028963_0027_0FDDBD61A3BBF6E8">
<HEAD>CHAP. VII. </HEAD>
<ARGUMENT>
<P>All the Charges in the foregoing Chapter partial, and <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word"> free from mi&s;repre&s;entation&mdash;Buffon and M. de Pauw's De&s;criptions refuted&mdash;Errors as to their Want of Beard&mdash;Form and A&s;pect&mdash;Con&s;titution and Corporal Abilities&mdash;Labour and Indu&s;try&mdash;Mental Qualities.&mdash; M. de Pauw's Proofs of their Cowardice refuted&mdash;In|&s;tances of Courage, Fortitude and Eloquence&mdash;Repre&s;ent|ations of COLUMBUS&mdash;Conclu&s;ions concerning their Ca|pacities&mdash;Ingenuity.&mdash;Tokens of Science.&mdash;Specimen of their Morality.</P>
