<P>The bill was brought in; and on the fir&s;t reading, Mr. Charles Town&s;end &s;poke in its favour. He took notice of &s;everal things that colonel Barre had &s;aid in his &s;peech again&s;t it; and then concluded with the fol|lowing or like words: "And now will the&s;e Ameri|cans, children planted by our care; nouri&s;hed up by our
