<NOTE PLACE="marg"><HI>June</HI> 1.</NOTE> but it had been little attended to. T<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters"> a&s;&s;embly began their &s;e&s;&s;ion by inquiries into the <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word"> of the magazine. It had been broken into by &s;om<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> the town&s;men; for which rea&s;on &s;pring gun<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> had <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word"> placed there by the governour, which di&s;charged the<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">|&s;elves upon the offenders at their entran<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters"> the&s;e circum&s;tances,
